post_text:
Trojans vs Greenbacks.

Game Day Procedure:
- Masks must be worn by all spectators for entrance into contests. For outdoor activities masks are required for admission, and must be worn when social distancing cannot be maintained.
- Temperature checks will be done at all entrances. No admission if a temperature is about 100 F.
- Seating capacity will be limited to 4 spectators per participant. Participants will be given 4 vouchers to distribute. Tickets will be distributed to the athletes at practice. Upon arrival at the activity, present your vouchers to the workers, pay the admission fee, then gain access to the event.
- Spectators should remain in family groups with physical social distancing between groups. All children, including students must remain with their parents/guardians. Children will not be allowed to run around the grounds unsupervised.
- Entrance Fees-$6 Adult $4 Children‚ÄîNO CNC League Passes. #girardtrojans #girardtrojanfootball

USD 248 Special Board Meeting

USD 248-Girard Board of Education will meet at the GMS/GHS Media Center, in Girard, at 8 am on Thursday, July 30, 2020 for a Special Board Meeting. The purpose of this meeting will be to amend the 2020-2021 School Calendar, to approve the 2020-2021 Return to School policy guide, and an Executive Session for personnel discussion.

If you have any questions, please call the USD 248 District Office at 620-724-4325.

Due to request from repeat customers and new interest, we are excited to place a 3rd order for the Trojan Face mask fundraiser for GHS-FBLA and GHS Dance Team.

Email: GirardTrojanMasks@gmail.com

Send your name, contact phone number, how many masks you wish to order, and if you wish the proceeds for your order to benefit FBLA or Dance Team. #girardtrojans

Please place your orders by August 1st. You will receive an auto response at the time of your order and another reply email after we receive delivery with pick-up information.

Thank you for supporting our GHS activities! Go Trojans!

post_text:
üèàGMS Footballüèà

MS football camp begins Monday July 6 from 9-10 a.m. Cost is $25.

Per the governors orders, athletes and coaches will be required to wear masks when social distancing can not be maintained. Athletes may pull down their mask when social distancing can be maintained or while running.

Coaches will provide extra water breaks and be vigilant when kids are running to make sure all kids are safe. We encourage kids to bring their own water bottles with their name on the bottle. Kids may bring their own mask or face covering. USD #248 will provide masks for those that do not have a mask.

GHS Class of 2020 ‚Äì‚Äì Craig Crespino Scholarships

Two scholarships in memory of Craig Crespino are awarded locally each year, one sponsored by family and friends and funded by the Craig Crespino Memorial Golf Tournament and one funded by Coach Crespino's classmates the St. Mary's‚ÄìColgan Class of 1979. The recipients of this year's Craig Crespino Memorial Scholarships are:

Megan Shireman (Craig Crespino Memorial Golf Tournament)

Mackenzie Coester (SMC Class of 1979)

Due to COVID-19 the 2020 Craig Crespino Memorial Golf Tournament has been cancelled--this tournament helps provide the funding of this scholarship. If you would like to contribute to the 2020-21 scholarship fund, you can contact Erica (Crespino) Harris or send donations to Mike Carpenter at P.O. Box 8, Girard, KS. 66743. The Crespino family appreciates your support in keeping Coach Crespino's legacy alive.

Seniors,



Thank you for being patient, we are almost there!



We plan to have your graduation ceremony on Friday, July 10th at 8 PM outdoors on the Frank Jameson Field. If weather prevents that ceremony from occurring, we will move it to the next night (July 11th) at the same time.



We will have a graduation practice on Monday, July 6th at 8 PM. Please attend.



Many of you have asked about diplomas and reimbursement of Seniors Fees. All of those will be distributed the day of the ceremony. If you need these items before that date, please contact the GHS office and set up an appointment.



A letter will be coming in the mail soon with all of the details for the week.





Go Trojans!



Mr. Ferguson

Senior Spotlight ‚Äì GHS Class of 2020

Courtney Rae Wilson

Courtney Rae Wilson resides in Walnut and has attended Girard schools. Her three siblings include Brandon Wilson, Cyndi Wilson and David Lewis.

During high school Courtney was involved in FCCLA and Kayettes. She was a FCCLA board member her junior and senior year and a Kayettes board member her senior year. She was also a member of Drama and Forensics her freshman year.

Courtney was also a Renaissance cardholder.

Outside of school Courtney enjoys reading, volunteering and spending time with friends. She is a member of the Girard Medical Center Youth Leadership Program and works as a CNA at Medicalodges Girard.

After graduation Courtney plans to attend PSU through the FSCC Qualified Admissions Program.

Senior Spotlight ‚Äì GHS Class of 2020

Aubrey Elizabeth Scott

Aubrey Scott, daughter of Greg and Melissa Scott, resides in Hepler and has attended Girard schools. Her four siblings include Tasha Fox, Erica Kern, Vanessa Birney and Trevor Scott, who are all GHS graduates.

During high school Aubrey was involved in FCCLA, FEA, FFA, Kayettes, Student Council and SADD. She was an FFA Greenhand and Intermediate Officer her freshman and sophomore year and a Kayettes board member and treasurer, FFA Student Council representative and SADD secretary her junior and senior year. She was also a student aide for two years, a GHS mentor and a football Homecoming queen candidate.

Her academic honors included being a four-year Renaissance cardholder, NHS member and honor roll recipient.

Outside of school Aubrey enjoys being a part of the Cross Trails Ministry, participating on the CTM Rodeo team and going to school activities.
After graduation Aubrey plans to attend LCC and later continue her education at PSU.

Antonia Felicia Pizarro

Antonia Felicia Pizarro, daughter of Luis and Rena Pizarro, resides in Erie and has attended Fredonia, Erie, and Girard schools. Her three siblings include Noemi, Juan, and Nahilea.

Antonia was also a four-year Renaissance cardholder.

Outside of school Antonia enjoys listening to music, singing, writing, and walking her dog.

After graduation she plans to attend PSU and pursue a bachelor's degree in elementary education.

Senior Spotlight ‚Äì GHS Class of 2020

Matthew Christopher Pike

Matthew Christoper Pike, son of Patricia and Chris Pike, resides in Girard and has attended Girard schools. He has three siblings Latricia, Deanna and Anthony.

During high school Matthew was involved in FFA and SkillsUSA. He was also a member of the FFA livestock judging team and the FSCC Masonry Technology program.

He participated in football his freshman and senior year.

His honors included being an Athlete of the Month, a football Homecoming queen escort and a Renaissance cardholder. He also placed second at SkillsUSA.

Outside of school Matthew enjoys feeding cows, driving four wheelers and eating food.

After graduation Matthew plans to attend Pratt Community College and pursue a degree in Electrical Power Technology.

post_text: Orin Weiss is the first student in either middle or high school to achieve the "choir karate black belt" award this year! To win the choir karate black belt, students must complete a series of 12 quizzes without missing a single question. Some topics include note identification, rhythm reading, and key signatures. The final quiz for black belt is cumulative and contains 68 questions, which Orin achieved at 100%! Congratulations, Orin!

GHS Class of 2020 ‚ÄìKansas Board of Regents

Scholars Curriculum Completers

Each year, the Kansas Board of Regents recognizes students who have completed its Scholars Curriculum, which includes:

4 credits of English

4 credits of Math (Algebra I or above)

3 credits of Science (Biology, Chemistry and Physics)

3 credits of Social Studies

2 credits of Foreign Language

This year throughout Kansas, 6262 students are being recognized for completing this curriculum. At Girard, seniors who completed the curriculum are:

Tricia Combs

Isabella Crumpacker

Michael Kmiec

DeLaney McFarland

Colby McManis

Hunter Ulbrich

Kansas Board of Regents

Scholars

In addition, the Kansas Board of Regents is recognizing the top 2641students who completed the scholars curriculum, based upon a combination of ACT Scores and Grade Point Average, as its State Scholars. These students across the state have an average ACT score of 30 and an average grade point average of 3.91. Girard High School has 3 designated State Scholars:

Tricia Combs

DeLaney McFarland

Colby McManis

Andrew Thomas Green, son of Regina Green and Bill Goff, resides in Girard and has attended McCune, Pittsburg, Arma, Wichita and Girard schools. His brother James and sister Audrey are both GHS graduates.

During high school, Andrew participated in Art Club, FBLA, FEA and Recycling Club. He was also a student aide and was involved in the mentor program. Andrew also participated in PSU Math Honor Day, PSU Math Relays and FSCC Math Relays.

His academic honors include being a four-year Renaissance cardholder, Boys State Delegate and an honor roll recipient.

Outside of school, Andrew enjoys playing video games, playing with his dogs, reading books and listening to music.

After graduation, Andrew plans to attend PSU and pursue a degree in
science and education with a major in accounting or medical science and a minor in math.

Senior Spotlight ‚Äì GHS Class of 2020

Joshua George Duling

Joshua George Duling, son of Rick and Barb Duling, resides in Girard and
has attended Girard schools. He has two brothers, Shane and Kyle, who are both GHS graduates.

During high school Josh was involved in Art Club, Pep Band, Jazz Band and Drama and Forensics. He was band treasurer and Class of 2020 president his junior year. As a band member he traveled to Orlando, Florida, to play at Disney‚Äôs Magic Kingdom; Branson, Missouri, to play in the Veterans Day parade; Little Rock, Arkansas, to play at an Arkansas Naturals Game and San Antonio, Texas, to play at Six Flags Fiesta Texas.

His honors included being a two-year drama and forensics state qualifier,
and four-year letterman in band.

Outside of school, Josh enjoys producing music and cinematography.

After graduation, Josh plans to spend his time working on production and
marketing.
